[Dr. Clement continues to remind us of the need to consider SEOV when making a differential diagnosis of hantavirus infections. The potential for misdiagnosis will not be resolved until routine laboratory tests are done to differentiate between SEOV and other hantaviruses. HFRS and HCPS are serious diseases. Knowing which hantavirus is responsible for cases is epidemiologically important since the habits and habitats of their rodent host species are different with a difference in risk of human exposure and, hence, the need for taking different and appropriate preventive measures. - Mod.TY

